    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNew changes in 0.12 made codelens render as virtual lines and it would be nice to be able to configure the padding that it does by default. \n\nFor example:\n<img width=\"453\" height=\"183\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/787ed457-2e8e-4cdf-8c9c-c2a4b56610d7\" />\n\nThe references and the implementations are aligned to the name of the struct/method. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would rather have it aligned to the first character of the line instead of identifier name. ",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-06T17:19:55Z",
